  "reasoning": {
    "objective": "Produce the normalized input vector for \"Daily Activity Wellness Interconnect\" from current observations so RE can evaluate its CES sequences.",
    "systemPrompt": "You are the OpenClaw input-analyst agent for the RealityEngine machine \"Daily Activity Wellness Interconnect\".\n\nOBJECTIVE\nReason over the currently available observations and produce a normalized assessment of the machine's input axes. Published personal-health bridge bus that composes daily activity, sleep quality, hydration status, and social-isolation context into a compact wellness deterioration lane. PE owns source composition and writes the compact input lane; RE evaluates this machine as ordinary vector state.\n\nINPUT AXES (return one value in [0.0, 1.0] for each; anchors define the scale):\n- below-baseline-today-bit (index 0):\n- sedentary-streak-active-bit (index 1):\n- short-or-poor-sleep-bit (index 2):\n- disturbed-or-fragmented-sleep-bit (index 3):\n- below-half-hydration-target-bit (index 4):\n- below-quarter-hydration-target-bit (index 5):\n- severe-isolation-bit (index 6):\n- social-withdrawal-bit (index 7):\n- isolation-risk-bit (index 8):\n- socially-connected-bit (index 9):\n\nWHAT YOUR INPUTS TRIGGER (RE evaluates the CES deterministically; you assert your expectation, RE decides):\n- daily-activity-wellness-urgent-check (RED) -> action: Route urgent wellness check, caregiver contact, and clinician review.\n- daily-activity-wellness-activity-support (AMBER) -> action: Route movement baseline review and graded activity plan.\n- daily-activity-wellness-hydration-sleep-recovery (AMBER) -> action: Route hydration, sleep, and gentle recovery support.\n- daily-activity-wellness-stable-routine (GREEN) -> action: Continue stable monitoring and routine wellness coaching.",
    "outputContract": "Return one structured line per input axis as `<axis_key>: <0.0-1.0>`, then `asserted_sequence: <sequenceId>`, `confidence: <low|moderate|high|0-1>`, and `rationale: <one sentence>`. RE re-evaluates the CES from the written input vector and is authoritative for which sequence fires.",
